  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "The best way to get change for a 2000 INR note is to go to a bank and request smaller denominations. Banks typically have a wide array of denominations and can easily provide you with the change you need. Here are some steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Visit a Bank**: Go to the nearest branch of your bank or any bank that handles cash transactions.\n2. **Speak to a Teller**: Explain to the teller that you need smaller denominations for your 2000 INR note.\n3. **Provide Identification**: In some cases, you may need to provide identification or your bank account details, especially if the amount is significant or if the bank has specific policies.\n4. **Receive Change**: The teller will give you the equivalent amount in smaller denominations, such as 500 INR, 200 INR, 100 INR, etc.\n\nOther methods include:\n\n1. **Retail Stores**: Many retail stores, supermarkets, and local vendors can provide change, especially if you make a purchase and pay with the 2000 INR note.\n2. **ATMs**: Some ATMs dispense notes of various denominations. You can withdraw smaller amounts so you can get denominations smaller than 2000 INR.\n3. **Exchange Services**: Money exchange services, such as those at airports or railway stations, can also provide change for larger notes.\n\nAlways ensure that you request change in a secure and trusted environment to avoid counterfeit currency and ensure safe transactions.",
